1 (1) in times of or on reasonable apprehension of imminent public crisis,
2 disaster, rioting, catastrophe, insurrection, invasion, tumult, or breach of peace;
3 (2) when martial law is declared;
4 (3) to enforce the laws; or
5 (4) to carry on any function of the militia of the State.
6 (c) (1) To enforce the laws, a member of the militia in State active duty has all
7 the authority of a peace or law enforcement officer.
8 (2) The authority of the member extends throughout the State during the
9 State active duty.
10 (d) Whenever the militia is in State active duty, the ranking officer of the militia
11 ordered into State active duty or that officer’s subordinates on State active duty shall:
12 (1) cooperate with local law enforcement authorities; or
13 (2) if the exigencies of the case require and subject only to order from the
14 Governor:
15 (i) direct and control local law enforcement authorities and the
16 Department of State Police; and
17 (ii) assume all the powers vested in these subordinated law
18 enforcement authorities.
19 (E) (1) (I) IN THIS SUBSECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE
20 MEANINGS INDICATED.
21 (II) “ACTIVE DUTY COMBAT” MEANS PERFORMING THE
22 FOLLOWING SERVICES IN THE ACTIVE FEDERAL MILITARY SERVICE OF THE UNITED
23 STATES:
24 1. PARTICIPATION IN AN ARMED CONFLICT;
25 2. PERFORMANCE OF A HAZARDOUS SERVICE RELATING
26 TO AN ARMED CONFLICT IN A FOREIGN STATE; OR
27 3. PERFORMANCE OF A DUTY THROUGH AN
28 INSTRUMENTALITY OF WAR.

HOUSE BILL 548 3
1 (III) “OFFICIAL DECLARATION OF WAR” MEANS AN OFFICIAL
2 DECLARATION OF WAR MADE BY THE U.S. CONGRESS UNDER ARTICLE I, § 8,
3 CLAUSE 11 OF THE U.S. CONSTITUTION.
4 (2) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, THE
5 GOVERNOR MAY NOT ORDER THE MILITIA OR ANY MEMBER OF THE MILITIA INTO
6 ACTIVE DUTY COMBAT UNLESS THE U.S. CONGRESS HAS PASSED AN OFFICIAL
7 DECLARATION OF WAR OR HAS TAKEN AN OFFICIAL ACTION UNDER ARTICLE I, § 8,
8 CLAUSE 15 OF THE U.S. CONSTITUTION TO EXPLICITLY CALL FORTH THE STATE
9 MILITIA OR ANY MEMBER OF THE STATE MILITIA TO EXECUTE THE LAWS OF THE
10 UNITED STATES, REPEL AN INVASION, OR SUPPRESS AN INSURRECTION.
11 (3) NOTHING IN THIS SUBSECTION MAY BE CONSTRUED TO LIMIT OR
12 PROHIBIT THE GOVERNOR FROM DEPLOYING THE MILITIA OR A MEMBER OF THE
13 MILITIA UNDER U.S.C. TITLE 32, DEFENSE SUPPORT OF CIVIL AUTHORITIES,
14 WITHIN THE UNITED STATES AND U.S. TERRITORIES.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
16 October 1, 2025.

